modules.description: Handles text indentation by offering functions to calculate, adjust, and normalize indentation levels in strings. Operates on raw string data and provides precise control over leading whitespace. Used to format code blocks, align log entries, and process structured text inputs.

Appends strings to a buffer, inserting current indentation at the start of new lines. Manages indentation levels with explicit increase and decrease operations. Used to generate formatted text output with consistent line breaks and nesting.
